razole, Glucosamine', NULL, 'Moderate', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/159041/', '[1] Townend JN, Doran J, Lote CJ, Davies MK "Peripheral haemodynamic effects of inhibition of prostaglandin synthesis in congestive heart failure and interactions with captopril." Br Heart J 73 (1995): 434-41[2] Ahmad S "Indomethacin-enalapril interaction: an alert." South Med J 84 (1991): 411-2[3] Silberbauer K, Stanek B, Templ H "Acute hypotensive effect of captopril in man modified by prostaglandin synthesis inhibition." Br J Clin Pharmacol 14 (1982): s87-93[4] "Product Information. Toradol (ketorolac)." Roche Laboratories, Nutley, NJ.[5] Morgan T, Anderson A "Interaction of indomethacin with felodipine and enalapril." J Hypertens 11 (1993): S338-9[6] Radack KL, Deck CC, Bloomfield SS "Ibuprofen interferes with the efficacy of antihypertensive drugs: a randomized, double-blind, placebo-controlled trial of ibuprofen compared with acetaminophen." Ann Intern Med 107 (1987): 628-35[7] "Product Information. Celebrex (celecoxib)." Searle, Chicago, IL.[8] Abdel-Haq B, Magagna A, Favilla S, Salvetti A "Hemodynamic and humoral interactions between perindopril and indomethacin in essential hypertensive subjects." J Cardiovasc Pharmacol 18 (1991): s33-6[9] "Product Information. Daypro (oxaprozin)." Searle, Skokie, IL.[10] Polonia J, Boaventura I, Gama G, Camoes I, Bernardo F, Andrade P, Nunes JP, Brandao F, Cerqueiragomes M "Influence of non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs on renal function and 24h ambulatory blood pressure-reducing effects of enalapril and nifedipine gastrointestinal therapeutic system in hypertensive patients." J Hypertens 13 (1995): 925-31[11] Seto S, Aoi W, Iwami K, et al "Effect of propranolol and indomethacin on the depressor action of captopril in patients with essential hypertension." Clin Exp Hypertens 9 (1987): 623-7[12] Allon M, Pasque CB, Rodriguez M "Interaction of captopril and ibuprofen on glomerular and t